# .gitattributes - line ending normalization for the Ascent repo
#
# Goal: keep all text files using LF in the repo, regardless of which OS
# committed them. Prevents the "LF will be replaced by CRLF" warning Dom saw
# when committing the v2 wk1 files from Windows.
#
# How this works:
#   * "text=auto eol=lf" means: Git treats matching files as text and forces
#     LF line endings in the repo. On checkout, working-copy line endings
#     follow the user's core.autocrlf setting (Windows defaults to CRLF in
#     working copy, which is fine -- Git converts back to LF on commit).
#   * Binary patterns get "binary" so Git doesn't try to diff or normalize.
#
# Scoped narrowly to the file types we actually use. Add new patterns as the
# repo grows; do NOT add a blanket "* text=auto" without considering the
# impact on existing files.

# Source code -- always LF in repo
*.js          text eol=lf
*.mjs         text eol=lf
*.ts          text eol=lf
*.jsx         text eol=lf
*.tsx         text eol=lf
*.html        text eol=lf
*.css         text eol=lf
*.json        text eol=lf
*.md          text eol=lf
*.yml         text eol=lf
*.yaml        text eol=lf

# Shell + Node tooling
*.sh          text eol=lf
.gitignore    text eol=lf
.gitattributes text eol=lf

# PowerShell scripts -- Windows-native, but LF works fine in PowerShell 5.1+
*.ps1         text eol=lf

# Documentation source
*.txt         text eol=lf

# Binary content -- never line-end normalized
*.pdf         binary
*.docx        binary
*.png         binary
*.jpg         binary
*.jpeg        binary
*.gif         binary
*.webp        binary
*.ico         binary
*.zip         binary
*.gz          binary
*.tar         binary
